Comment: Great clash idea, I underestimated its difficulty at first; still found it to be quite fun. The solution was easier than I thought:

n = int(input())
if n <= 0 or n >= 10: print("Error")
else:
    for i in range(n*2+1):
        g = []
        for j in range(n*2+1):
            g.append(max(abs(n-i), abs(n-j)))
        print(*g)

A bit more brutal, to avoid having to think about max and abs and correct indexing in Fastest mode:

N = 2 * n + 1
if n < 1 or n > 9:
    print('Error')
else:
    grid = np.full((N,N),n)
    for k in range(1,n+1):
        grid[k:N-k, k:N-k] = n-k
    for row in grid:
        print(*row)
